  "text": "Mechanisms relating stocking density and growth are not fully understood, but it is generally accepted that, when water quality is not affected by the increased number of fish per cubic meter, and food items are provided in sufficient amounts, differences in growth performance could be attributed to the onset of hierarchies and dominance relationships [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Moreover, intrinsic internal factors such as genotype or the interaction among genotype and ongrowing environment, could as well be related to growth performance [CITATION_3] .",
